                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12708609" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 12 May 2009 20:34:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andrew Purtell:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I think HLogEdit would still be needed for something like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1295&quot; title=&quot;Multi data center replication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1295&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1295&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, for noting the edit source so values are not re-replicated back to the peer.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;stack:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Can we do these markings as Types in the new KeyValue? Before serializing we could AND the key type with source. How many bits do you need?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Andrew Purtell:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t imagine more than 128 peer clusters for a replicator scenario, so 7 bits of Type would be enough, as long as they could be reserved somehow.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;stack: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Type is a byte only in KV. So, maximum you can have is 4, maybe 5 bits - smile.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12708610" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 12 May 2009 20:36:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So Type &amp;gt;&amp;gt; 4 &amp;amp; 0xF?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12708624" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 12 May 2009 21:04:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After discussion on IRC, HLogKey will be available for modification for replicator or transactional bits. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1295&quot; title=&quot;Multi data center replication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1295&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1295&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; presumes HLK will be serialized into the HLog.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12708629" author="stack" created="Tue, 12 May 2009 21:11:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chatting with Andrew on IRC, sounds like it would make more sense moving replicator needs into the HLogKey; this already keeps meta data on an edit &amp;#8211; the Table and Region &amp;#8211; so would seem more natural putting replication info in here.  Just need to make sure a replicating HBase can subclass HLog fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On remove HLogEdit, just got go ahead from Clint.  He thinks he can mark KVs with necessary transactional flags.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bringing this into 0.20.0 since it won&apos;t take much to do it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12708632" author="stack" created="Tue, 12 May 2009 21:19:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can&apos;t make this change before KeyValue becoming Writable&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12709164" author="stack" created="Wed, 13 May 2009 22:27:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that removes HKeyEdit.  Now we just put KeyValue into commit log value.  This patch breaks THBase but Clint said he&apos;d fix it later after the dust has settled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12709208" author="stack" created="Wed, 13 May 2009 23:22:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had to disable TestTransactions because it wasn&apos;t working after my commenting THBase&apos;s guts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
